(1) No registered seed importer shall import any prescribed seed into Zambia unless— (a) such seed is not restricted seed , the importation of which has been prohibited by regulation made under section thirty-nine; (b) such seed is not restricted seed , the importation of which has been made subject to conditions or limitations prescribed by regulation made under section thirty-nine and such prescribed conditions or limitations have not been fulfilled or performed; (c) such seed being restricted seed , the importation of which has been prohibited by regulation made under section thirty-nine, a permit for its importation has issued under the provisions of section forty-one; (d) such seed being restricted seed , the importation of which has been made subject to conditions or limitations prescribed by regulation made under section thirty-nine and such prescribed conditions or limitations have not been fulfilled or performed, a permit for its importation has issued under the provisions of section forty-one; (e) such seed conforms to the standards of germination and purity and other requirements prescribed therefor; (f) if such seed is packed in a container or containers, such container or containers comply with the requirements prescribed; (g) the genus, species and variety of such seed , and the country of its origin, is shown on an invoice or delivery note accompanying such seed at the time of its importation.
